pysum - A pygtk application for create and verify md5 and other checksum
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

This is a development version of pysum, some things are not finished

pysum depends on the Python runtime and associated libraries.

Python (>= 2.4) : http://www.python.org
PyGTK (>= 2.8) : http://www.pygtk.org

== To run pysum ==

You can find the source code of pysum in /src

To run, in a terminal use the following syntax:
$ cd src
$ python pysum.py

== Translations (i18n) ==

You can find the *.pot file and a spanish translation (.po and .mo files) in the /po directory.

You can translate the *.pot file and generate a *.mo file. You should copy the *.mo files into your locate directory. For example, if you use a translation into Spanish, copy the es.mo file to /usr/share/locale/es/LC_MESSAGES/pysum.mo
